ÈóÆÈ¢òÂéüÂõ†ÔºöThe issue could be with the response you are receiving from back-end. If it was working fine on the server then the problem could be with the response headers. Check the *Access-Control-Allow-Origin* (ACAO) in the response headers. Usually react's fetch API will throw fail to fetch even after receiving response when the response headers' ACAO and the origin of request won't match. 

Ëß£ÂÜ≥ÊñπÊ°àÔºö  If the API is using `express` for node you can use the simple `cors` package. If you want to make your site properly secure, consider using a whitelist for the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header.

